<HEAD>Snow Falls In Higher Elevations of West, Southwest; Fair In East</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By The Associated Press</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
   Snow fell in the mountainous areas of the West and Southwest
today as most of the East enjoyed fair skies.
   Snow advisories this morning were posted for several mountain
ranges, including the Cascades and Olympics of Washington; the
Cascades, Siskiyous and northern coastal range of Oregon; the Sierra
Nevada of California; the higher elevations of Arizona's central
mountains; the western and northern mountains through the northwest
plateau of New Mexico; and the mountains of Colorado.
   While skies were fair early this morning over the eastern
two-thirds of the nation, snow was falling in the mountains of
Colorado, northwest New Mexico, northern Arizona, central and
northern California, western Nevada, Oregon, Washington and
northwest Montana.
   Snow became rain in the lower elevations and extended across the
northern and central Pacific Coast, as well as southern Arizona.
   The nation's high temperature Thursday was 85 degrees at Cotulla,
Texas.
   Today's forecast called for rain, with snow in the higher
elevations, from northeast Montana across Idaho, Washington, Oregon
and northern California; thunderstorms, some possibly severe, from
eastern Oklahoma across central and western Texas into the lower
Mississippi Valley.
   Predicted highs: 20s in the mountains of southern Colorado; 30s
and 40s from northern and central New England into northeast New
York state, across upper Michigan, northwest Wisconsin, the upper
Mississippi Valley, northern Plains, the rest of the Rockies, Great
Basin, and northern Pacific Coast; 50s and 60s from southern New
England across the Carolinas, the rest of of the Great Lakes, Ohio
Valley, central Mississippi Valley, Kansas and Oklahoma, from
southwest Texas across the desert Southwest and the rest of the
Pacific Coast states; 80s in southern Texas; and 70s across the rest
of the nation.
   The nation's temperatures at 2 a.m. EST ranged from 11 degrees at
Casper, Wyo., to 72 at Kingsville, Texas.
   Other reports:
   _East: Atlanta 45 foggy; Boston 31 windy; Buffalo 29 fair;
Charleston, S.C. 40 fair; Cincinnati 41 cloudy; Cleveland 34 fair;
Detroit 36 fair; Miami 66 partly cloudy; New York 35 fair;
Philadelphia 30 fair; Pittsburgh 29 foggy; Portland, Maine 29 windy;
Washington 36 fair.
