<2ND_LINE>AM-MASH Hospital,0207</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Hospital Looks Like War Zone, So Workers Will Play MASH Characters</HEAD>
<DATELINE>KENNEWICK, Wash. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Employees at Kennewick General Hospital
say a multimillion-dollar remodeling project has left the place
looking like an Army field hospital, so they're going to play the
part.
   Employees have had to contend with portable lights hanging down
halls and plywood walls and ceilings in some places during
construction.
   They say it reminds them of the satirical movie and television
series ``MASH,'' short for Mobile Army Surgical Hospital.
   So next Friday they plan to come to work dressed as characters
from the later seasons of the TV show, set during the Korean War.
   Darlene Smolen, hospital marketing director, said administrator
Michael Frazier will play the part of Col. Sherman Potter. Ms.
Smolen said she's not sure if anyone is going to play the part of
Cpl. Maxwell Klinger, who wore dresses in an effort to get
discharged from the Army.
   The employees' cafeteria will serve food reminiscent of the chow
that disgusted the MASH characters, including creamed chipped beef
on toast, Ms. Smolen said.
   She said the simulation is a way for hospital workers to laugh at
the construction disruptions instead of getting angry.
</TEXT>
