<HEAD>U.S. Welcomes South African Move on Mandela</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The State Department welcomed on Friday the
decision of the South African government not to send African
National Congress Leader Nelson Mandela back to prison after his
treatment for tuberculosis at a private clinic is concluded.
   The government said that Mandela, who has spent 26 years in
prison, will be transferred to some form of house arrest.
