<HEAD>Explosion, Fire on Italian Navy Frigate Kills One Sailor</HEAD>
<DATELINE>ROME (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   An explosion and fire Friday struck an Italian navy
frigate that recently returned from the Persian Gulf, killing one
sailor, state television said.
   A navy official said two or three sailors were injured, but
Italian TV reported four were hurt.
   The fire appeared to have broken out in the room where the dead
sailor was found aboard the Mistrale, which had returned from duty
protecting Italian shipping during the war between Iran and Iraq,
said the navy official, who spoke on condition of anonymity.
