<DATELINE>NASHVILLE, Tenn. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Actor David Keith says nothing on a movie
set matches the exhilaration he feels when the University of
Tennessee wins a football game.
   Keith grew up in Knoxville, where the school's main campus is
located, and attended the university. His devotion to the team is so
keen that he visits the players in the locker room and stands on the
sidelines during games. He plans to be with the team during the
Tennessee-Vanderbilt game Saturday in Nashville.
   ``When we lose, it's like I lose. It's devastating. It ruins
me,'' said Keith, who has appeared in such movies as ``An Officer
and a Gentleman,'' ``Heartbreak Hotel'' and ``Firestarter.''
   ``But when we win, it's a feeling you can't duplicate on a movie
set or a record album or anything else,'' he said. ``I guess they
call it the thrill of victory. There's nothing else like it.''
