<HEAD>New Talks Set On U.S.-Soviet Grain Deal</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A team of U.S. negotiators is heading for
Moscow this weekend for another try at reaching a new long-term
grain agreement, the White House said Friday.
   The announcement by the U.S. trade representative's office said
the next negotiating sesssion is scheduled for Monday, Nov. 28. Alan
F. Holmer, deputy U.S. trade representative, will lead the
delegation.
