<HEAD>Ford Offers Cash Rebates On Bronco II, Ranger</HEAD>
<DATELINE>DETROIT (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Ford Motor Co. said Friday it is offering cash
rebates through Jan. 31 of up to $600 on 1989 Bronco II compact
utility vehicles and up to $500 on 1989 Ranger compact pickup trucks.
   The rebates were effective Friday and continue through Dec. 31,
the company said.
   Ford will offer $600 cash allowances on 1989 four-wheel drive
Bronco II models, $500 rebates on two-wheel-drive Bronco II's, and
$400 rebates on Ranger S models.
   On 1988 models, the company offers rebates of $400 on
four-wheel-drive Bronco II's, $300 on two-wheel-drive Bronco II's,
and $400 on all Rangers.
   Ford said previous cash-allowance programs on the trucks expired
Nov. 24.
